headline: Think GE Aerospace Is Expensive? This Chart Might Change Your Mind.
summary: Selling airplane engines isn't really a profitable business, as engines are typically sold at a loss.  The major commercial engine manufacturers, such as GE Aerospace, RTX, and Rolls-Royce, make their money through the long-term stream of higher-margin aftermarket/services revenue generated on long-term contracts.  Given that airplane engines can be utilized for over 40 years, it's clear GE will generate a long tail of earnings and cash flow for every engine sold or already installed in the global airline fleet.
